  "prompt": "What are the top rated Hollywood movies in 2017?",
  "response": "The top-rated Hollywood movies of 2017 based on critical acclaim and audience reception typically include:\n\n1. **Get Out** - Directed by Jordan Peele, this horror film received widespread praise for its social commentary and originality.\n2. **Dunkirk** - Directed by Christopher Nolan, this war film was lauded for its stunning visuals and compelling storytelling.\n3. **Lady Bird** - Directed by Greta Gerwig, this coming-of-age film won critical acclaim for its humor, emotion, and performances.\n4. **The Shape of Water** - Directed by Guillermo del Toro, this fantasy romance film received high praise for its unique story and visual beauty.\n5. **Call Me by Your Name** - Directed by Luca Guadagnino, this romantic drama was celebrated for its performances and emotional depth.\n6. **Blade Runner 2049** - Directed by Denis Villeneuve, this sci-fi film was commended for its cinematography, special effects, and narrative.\n7. **Logan** - Directed by James Mangold, this superhero film was appreciated for its mature storytelling and character depth.\n8. **Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri** - Directed by Martin McDonagh, this drama was recognized for its strong script and powerful performances.\n9. **Coco** - Directed by Lee Unkrich, this animated film received acclaim for its heartwarming story and cultural depiction.\n10. **Wonder Woman** - Directed by Patty Jenkins, this superhero film was praised for its direction, performances, and strong female lead.\n\nThese films stand out for their high ratings, critical accolades, and impact on audiences.",
